SYMPTOM_TEXT: Foetal exposure during pregnancy; Breech presentation; This is an observational study case, initially received from other health professional on 23-Dec-2019, concerning a foetus subject, whose mother was a 31-year-old subject of body weight: 174 lbs, height: 68 inches and body mass index (BMI): 26.5, enrolled in a prospective observational safety study.   The subject's mother current conditions included body mass index (BMI) high and history of chronic hypertension.   The subject's mother concomitant medications included Prenatal vitamin (minerals not specific (nos), vitamins (nos)) for pregnancy.  The subject's mother had two previous pregnancies with two full term live births. The subject's mother did not have any history of offspring with major congenital malformation (MCM) and no paternal or maternal history with MCMs. The subject's mother did not use tobacco, alcohol or illicit drugs during pregnancy. The paternal age was not reported.  The subject's mother last menstrual period (LMP) date was on 21-Feb-2019, The type of pregnancy was singleton. The subject's mother estimated delivery date (EDD) was 28-Nov-2019 and corrected estimated date of delivery (CEDD) was not reported.   On 23-Apr-2019, ultrasound was performed, no major MCMs was noted.  On 23-May-2019, sequential one and nuchal translucency were performed, no major MCMs was noted.  On 19-Jun-2019, sequential two was performed, no major MCMs was noted.  On 23-Jul-2019, maternal foetal medicine anatomy scan was performed, no major MCMs was noted.  On 23-Sep-2019, at approximately 35 weeks of gestation, the subject's mother received Flu Vaccine Egg Split QIV CSL (Afluria QIV) [influenza vaccine, batch number: P100112488, dose, route of administration, expiry date and anatomical location: not reported] (explicitly coded as �Foetal exposure during pregnancy') for an unknown indication.  On unspecified date in 2019, the pregnancy status was collected and it was noted breech presentation.  At the time of this report, the outcome of the event breech presentation was not reported.  The event of breech presentation was considered serious due the criterion of medical significance.  The reporter did not provide causality assessment.  This case is linked with case 201907452 corresponding mother case.  Company comment: Reportedly, breech presentation was associated with Afluria QIV. The subject's mother was administered vaccine at approximately 35 weeks of gestation and the event was noted on an unspecified date in 2019. Chronology needs more clarification. Most breech presentations seem to be chance occurrences. However, in up to 15% of cases, it may be due to foetal or uterine causes (such as multiparity, in presented case). Therefore, causal role of the suspect vaccine is assessed as not related. Foetal exposure during pregnancy is assessed as unrelated per company's conventions.; Sender's Comments: Reportedly, breech presentation was associated with Afluria QIV. The subject's mother was administered vaccine at approximately 35 weeks of gestation and the event was noted on an unspecified date in 2019. Chronology needs more clarification. Most breech presentations seem to be chance occurrences. However, in up to 15% of cases, it may be due to foetal or uterine causes (such as multiparity, in presented case). Therefore, causal role of the suspect vaccine is assessed as not related. Foetal exposure during pregnancy is assessed as unrelated per company's conventions.

Pre-term delivery; Retained placenta with postpartum hemorrhage; Retained placenta with postpartum hemorrhage; Eclampsia; Mild pre-eclampsia; Vaccine exposure during pregnancy; This is an observational study case, initially received from other health professional on 20-Dec-2019, concerning a 32-year-old pregnant, female subject of body weight 150 lbs, height 66 inches and body mass index (BMI) 24.2,  enrolled in, a prospective observational safety study.  The subject's medical history included anxiety, depression and gestational diabetes.   The subject's concomitant medications included trazodone and sertraline, both used for anxiety and depression and Prenatal vitamins (unspecified vitamins) as supplement.  The subject had one previous pregnancy that ended as elective abortion.  The subject had no maternal/paternal history with major congenital malformation (MCM).  The subject's last menstrual period (LMP) date was 03-Mar-2019. The type of pregnancy was singleton. The subject's estimated delivery date (EDD) and corrected estimated delivery date (CEDD) were both 08-Dec-2019. The subject did not consume tobacco, alcohol and illicit-drugs during pregnancy.  On 02-Jul-2019, the subject performed Inheritest and maternal serum alpha-fetoprotein (MSAFP/serum markers) no and no MCM was noted.  On 10-Jul-2019 and on 10-Sep-2019, the subject underwent ultrasound and no MCM was noted.  On 16-Oct-2019, at gestational age of 32 weeks, the patient was administered Afluria QIV [influenza vaccine, batch number: P100118566, dose, route of administration, anatomical location and expiration date: not reported] for influenza immunisation (explicitly coded as 'Vaccine exposure during pregnancy').  On 25-Oct-2019, nine days after vaccination, the subject developed mild pre-eclampsia. On the same day, the subject underwent ultrasound and no MCM was noted.  On 31-Oct-2019, the subject started treatment with betamethasone for pre-eclampsia at a dose of 12.5 mg, twice a day via intramuscular route of administration.  On an unspecified date in Nov-2019, the patient developed eclampsia.  On 10-Nov-2019, at gestational age of 36 weeks, the subject vaginally delivered female neonate. The subject had retained placenta and experienced postpartum hemorrhage. The birth weight of the neonate was 2183 g, there were no data for head circumference and length. Appearance, pulse, grimace, activity and respiration (APGAR) score at one minute was 4, at five minutes was 7 and no data was reported for APGAR score at ten minutes. No MCM was identified at birth.  At the time of initial report, the outcome of all events, except vaccine exposure during pregnancy, was not reported.  This case is linked to case 201907460 (the corresponding child case).  The events of eclampsia, pre-eclampsia, preterm delivery and retained placenta with haemorrhage were considered serious due to the criterion of medical significance.  The reporter did not provide causality assessment to Afluria QIV.  Company comment: The subject experienced eclampsia, pre-eclampsia, premature delivery, postpartum haemorrhage and retained placenta associated with administration of Afluria QIV. The patient was administered vaccine at approximately 32 weeks of gestation. Chronology is plausible. However, causality was highly confounded by medical history of gestational diabetes. Regarding the events postpartum haemorrhage and retained placenta, risk factors (age over 30 and premature delivery) may have contributed to development of the events. Causal role of the suspect vaccine cannot be totally excluded and is assessed as unlikely related. Vaccine exposure during pregnancy is assessed as unrelated per company's conventions.; Sender's Comments: The subject experienced eclampsia, pre-eclampsia, premature delivery, postpartum haemorrhage and retained placenta associated with administration of Afluria QIV. The patient was administered vaccine at approximately 32 weeks of gestation. Chronology is plausible. However, causality was highly confounded by medical history of gestational diabetes. Regarding the events postpartum haemorrhage and retained placenta, risk factors (age over 30 and premature delivery) may have contributed to development of the events. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Did not feel insertion of needle.  Upon injection, felt hot, burning pain flow down the interior of upper arm.  3 hours post-injection ? upper left arm hurting, took Tylenol.  7 hours post-injection ? arm and shoulder hurting so much that it was very difficult to remove pullover shirt, took Tylenol.  10 hours post-injection ? arm and shoulder pain was 10 on a scale of 1 to 10; very difficult to sleep.  11 hours post-injection ? some nausea, pulse rate was 79 (normal at rest for me is 59), got up to go to bathroom, fainted, woke up on floor about 30 minutes later, extremely difficult to get up to sitting position because of pain / weakness in arms.  12 hours post-injection ? severe pain in upper arm and shoulder blade and back of neck, shivering, thirsty, clammy, heavy breathing, (no chest pain, no shoulder pain, and no headache, so ruled out heart attack - but the reaction was severe enough that we considered this possibility), no signs of stroke, slight nosebleed resulting from fall.  By 16 hours post-injection, felt minor bump on head and bump on left knee, and later noticed some hurting in jaw when trying to chew (all presumably caused by fainting fall).  2 days post-injection ? rash at injection site which looks like online photos of shingles rash, left eyelid discolored (presumably caused by fainting fall).  Rash did not disappear until 11 days post-injection.  From 2 days post-injection, and still continuing at 2 weeks post-injection, pain between right shoulder blade and base of neck, painful to sleep on sides or stomach, and periodical pain in shoulder blade / base of neck area that interfered with sleep.  Unable to determine whether shoulder blade / base of neck pain is due to vaccination or due to fainting fall.

On 12/23/19, patient came in with her mother. Mother reported that "almost immediately" while sitting in the waiting room after receiving the vaccine, patient started to have numbness and tingling on the left side of her face. Mother reported that patient did not state this until they left Health Department and were in their vehicle, approximately around 3:20-3:25pm. Patient stated that her throat was "starting to close up". Mother contacted Health Department via telephone while in their vehicle at 3:38pm to report adverse event and inquired about what to do. RN stated to go to the nearest Emergency Room if Mom wanted patient to be assessed and to seek medical treatment if needed.  Follow up phone call by RN on 12/30/19 at 12:00pm: Mother stated she did not go to the Emergency Room because patient was "calming down" once they got home and patient did not appear to need emergent medical care. Mother stated that patient has history of "complex migraines" and the symptoms patient experiences with migraines were similar to the symptoms she was having after vaccination, therefore Mother was unsure if vaccine triggered complex migraine or if it was separate.   When arrived home approx. 45 minutes after leaving Health Department, mother gave patient 25 mg tablet Benadryl by mouth one time as a precaution. Mother states that patients symptoms resolved without any further medication and no other symptoms appeared.
CUR_ILL: Denies illness at time of vaccination and one month prior to vaccination
ALLERGIES: No Known Drug allergies Food allergies to: Tree nuts, cantaloupe, citrus peels

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 12/23/19, patient came into Health Department with mother and three other siblings to receive immunizations. Patient received two immunizations; Influenza Seasonal Quadrivalent (Fluzone) and Inactivated Polio Virus. According to patient immunization record and registry, patient had received 5 vaccines with polio. After reviewing records and the CDC immunization guidance documents, it was determined that the last two polio vaccines patient previously received did not have enough spacing in between vaccination dose #4 and #5 and dose #5 did not count as enough coverage for patient. After discussing this with mother, mother requested 6th dose of polio to be administered on this date as well.  Mother reported that patient did not complain of any symptoms until they left the Health Department and were in the vehicle, when his older sister asked if anyone else had side effects of vaccines. Patient and family left the Health Department at approximately 3:20-3:25pm. Mother stated that patient "claims the side of his face felt numb and his throat was closing". Mother stated she is "not sure if he was really experiencing those side effects and took it with a grain of salt because he often wants to be like his siblings". Mother contacted Health Department via telephone while in their vehicle at 3:38pm to report patient and siblings adverse events and inquired about what to do. RN stated to go to the nearest Emergency Room if Mom wanted patient to be assessed and seek medical treatment if needed.  Follow up phone call by RN on 12/30/19 at 12:00pm: Mother stated she did not go to the Emergency Room because patients symptoms "were minor" and again stated that she was unsure if he was truly experiencing symptoms or "was trying to be like his siblings". Mother stated that when they arrived home, approximately 45 minutes after leaving the Health Department, mother gave patient 25 mg tablet Benadryl by mouth one time as a precaution. Mother stated that patient did not complain of any more symptoms and it resolved.  Mother also wanted to make note that patient is not biologically related to his other two siblings who also experienced the same adverse event on 12/23/19.
CUR_ILL: Mother denies patient had any illnesses at time of vaccination and the month prior to vaccination.

Vaccine given Thursday. Sunday while outside playing and doing farm chores patient started falling down repeatedly at a walk and a run.  The next day she started holding her hands in a fist, high stepping in her right leg, limping with an abnormal gait and complaining about a tingling feeling in her feet.  I called doctors office and they told me to give her ibuprofen and not let her run.  10 days later she was evaluated for headaches and referred to neurology for evaluation of headaches and neuro signs that followed vaccines. 3 months later on December 3rd she was evaluated by the pediatric neurology department. She was diagnosed with migraines but by the time she was evaluated her neuro signs were gone with just occasional limping in her right leg and weakness noted in her right hand by School.  This is not the first time she has had issues with neuro signs after her vaccines. On November 11, 2014 she received vaccines at Pediatrics, DTap-Hib-IPV, Rotovirus and pneumococcal. Within an hour of vaccinations she had hemorrhagic diarrhea. Approximately 2 weeks later she loss use of her right arm. It was blown off by the doctor at Pediatrics and later thought to be viral. On 2/26/16 vaccinated for DTap pneumococcal and HIb and continuously fell down. Was told by nurse it was just a clumsy child

An 81 year old man with MDS (for which he has received many transfusions over the past 2 to 3 years) received Shingrix vaccine on 12/26/2019. The next morning he was so weak he could not get out of bed or even sit up. 911 was called and took him to the ER. Although the doctors were told about the Shingrix shot the previous day they diagnosed him as having an 'underlying infection' and started him on IV antibiotics. The next day 12/28/2019 he felt much better, could walk unassisted. The doctors then said his white cell count was normal, stopped the antibiotics and discharged him home the next morning 12/29/2019. I do not have access to the lab tests done. It is unknown whether or not Shingrix caused the severe weakness that he experienced but no other cause is known. His hemoglobin was 10 which for him is good.
CUR_ILL: does not smoke or drink alcohol

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Tuesday, October 22,  I woke up with weakness (especially in limbs), joint stiffness, aching muscles, shortness of breath, and feeling like I was going to faint.  Within the week, I had visited my general practitioner three times and the emergency room once. Unfortunately, there was no real diagnosis except generalized anxiety, colitis,  hematuria, and low pancreatic enzymes. I continued with all of the above symptoms plus extreme diarrhea for seven days. After the initial seven days, I felt some better for six days and then got sick again. This time, it was many of the same symptoms such as muscle weakness, dizziness, and diarrhea with the addition of  headache, stiffness in neck, insomnia, and confusion when waking up. Also, it felt as if I could feel every nerve ending in my body. It has taken me two months to begin to feel like myself again. I am still having weakness and aching in my muscles particularly in my limbs and neck, along with unsteadiness.
LAB_DATA: 10/22- spirometry, electrocardiogram, CBC, chest xray- normal 10/23- CBC, Platelets, and At Diff, CMP, Amylase, Lipase- normal; urinalysis (hematuria) 10/25- Abdominal Ultrasound - slight "starry sky" appearance of the liver. No acute abnormality 11/05- urinalysis (hematuria) 11/06-CT Abdomen  pelvis w/wo IV contrast - normal 11/12- CBC, urinalysis (hematuria) 11/26- urinalysis (hematuria) 12/17- cystoscopy - normal

Delivery at gestational age of 36.7; Vaccine exposure during pregnancy; Gestational hypertension; This is an observational study case, initially received from other health professional on 23-Dec-2019, concerning a 22-year-old, female pregnant subject of body weight: 136 lbs, height: 63.6 inches and body mass index (BMI): 23.6 enrolled in a prospective observational safety study on pregnancy utcomes in women immunized with seasonal cell culture influenza trivalent (TIVc) or quadrivalent (QIVc) vaccine during pregnancy.  The subject's historical condition included bacterial vaginosis.   The subject's current conditions included nausea, depression, epilepsy and anxiety. The subject was RhD negative.   The subject's concomitant medications included folic acid as supplement, Diclegis (doxylamine succinate, pyridoxine hydrochloride) for nausea, Rhogam (anti-D immunoglobulin) as Rh-negative vaccine, Lamictal (lamotrigine) for epilepsy, Zoloft (sertraline hydrochloride) for depression, Flagyl (metronidazole benzoate) for bacterial vaginosis and hydroxyzine for anxiety.  The subject had one previous pregnancy which ended as spontaneous abortion. The subject had no maternal/paternal history with major congenital malformations (MCM).    The subject's last menstrual period (LMP) date was 10-Mar-2019. The type of pregnancy was singleton. The subject's estimated delivery date (EDD) and corrected estimated delivery date (CEDD) were both 15-Dec-2019. The subject did not consume tobacco, alcohol and illicit-drugs during pregnancy.  On 03-Jun-2019, the subject performed nuchal translucency and first trimester screen and no MCM was noted.  On 01-Jul-2019, the subject performed second trimester screen and maternal serum alpha-fetoprotein (MSAFP/serum markers) and no MCM was noted.  On 22-Jul-2019, the subject performed anatomy ultrasound and no MCM was noted.  On 17-Sep-2019, at gestational age of 27 weeks, the subject was administered Flu Vaccine Cell Subunit QIV NVD (influenza vaccine, subunit influenza virus vaccine polyvalent, batch number: 261200, dose: 0.5 mL, route of administration, anatomical location and expiry date: not reported) (explicitly coded as �Vaccine exposure during pregnancy') for influenza immunisation.  On the same day, the subject was also administered a non-company co-suspect vaccine TDAP [diphtheria vaccine toxoid, pertussis vaccine acellular, tetanus vaccine toxoid, dose: 0.5 ml, route of administration: intramuscular, anatomical location, batch number and expiry date: not reported] for vaccination.  On an unspecified date in 2019, after vaccination, the subject developed gestational hypertension.   On 22-Nov-2019, at gestational age of 36.7 weeks, the subject vaginally delivered live male neonate. The birth weight of the neonate was 3232 g, no data reported for head circumference and length. Appearance, pulse, grimace, activity and respiration (APGAR) score at one minute was 8, at five minutes was 9 and no data was reported for APGAR score at ten minutes. No MCM was identified at birth.  The event of preterm delivery was considered serious due to the criterion of medically significance.  The reporter did not provide causality assessment to Flucelvax QIVc.  This case is linked to case 201907469 (corresponding child case).  Company comment: Reportedly, gestational hypertension and premature delivery were associated with Flucelvax QIVc. Vaccine was administered at 27 weeks of gestation. Chronology is plausible. Causality was confounded by patient's obstetrical history of previous spontaneous abortion, non-company co-suspect vaccine TDAP administered on the same day and concomitant drugs used during pregnancy. Causal role of the suspect vaccine cannot be excluded and is assessed as related. Vaccine exposure during pregnancy is assessed as unrelated per company's conventions.; Sender's Comments: Reportedly, gestational hypertension and premature delivery were associated with Flucelvax QIVc. Vaccine was administered at 27 weeks of gestation. Chronology is plausible. Causality was confounded by patient's obstetrical history of previous spontaneous abortion, non-company co-suspect vaccine TDAP administered on the same day and concomitant drugs used during pregnancy. Causal role of the suspect vaccine cannot be excluded and is assessed as related. Vaccine exposure during pregnancy is assessed as unrelated per company's conventions.

Patient received his Kinrix and Proquad in his left thigh on 12/27/19.  Patient came in with his father on 12/30/19 due to redness and swelling of his left thigh.  He denied pain, had no limp, no fever and the swelling was improved since 12/29/19.  I measured the red area to be 16 cm down his thigh by 23 cm across.  It was slightly warm to the touch but non-tender and pt was using his legs fully, squatting spontaneously during the visit.  He had a very small, mobile non-tender lymph node in left inguinal area.  No streaking.  Discussed with patient's father that sometimes we see a localized skin reaction related to the diptheria in the vaccine.  Recommend continue Benadryl for 48 hours and warm compresses.  If fever, pain, not walking normally, return to clinic to consider giving antibiotics.   Since he is doing better with Benadryl, we chose to not start antibiotics today.

shingles; PHN/throbbing pain and residual nerve demage; Information has been received from a lawyer concerning a case in litigation and refers to female patient of an unknown age. No information regarding the patient's medical history, concurrent conditions and concomitant medications was reported. On 27-FEB-2018, the patient was inoculated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) (dose, route of administration, vaccination site, lot # and expiry date were not specified) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). On an unknown date in 2018 (reported as "less than two (2) months after receiving zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX)), the patient suffered debilitating injuries including painful and debilitating shingles as well as post herpetic neuralgia (PHN), significant throbbing pain and residual nerve damage. All of these injuries were caused by zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX). As a direct and proximate result of the Company's defective zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, the patient's symptoms have resulted in physical limitations not present prior to using the Company's product and caused by the zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine. The patient also experienced mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of her condition and has suffered economic losses due to her inability to work. As a result of the manufacture, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient sustained severe and disfiguring personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of Merck's wrongful conduct, the patient suffered serious, progressive, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of the Company's conduct, the patient has suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of the events was not recovered. The causality was related.  The events of shingles and PHN were considered to be disabling.

On 24-OCT-2019, the patient was vaccinated with improperly stored measles, mumps, and rubella (wistar ra 27-3) virus vaccine, live (M-M-R II) (strength, dose and frequency were not reported) lot # R031680, expiration date 01-NOV-2020. She stated that they gave her epinephrine, steroids, and Benadryl in the emergency room. She recently had cataracts surgery so she had given herself her eye drops and she was suspecting this had something to do with the eye drops. She stated that one eye drop was Prednisolone, and one was an antibiotic and the other was an antiinflammatory. She stated that she had checked with her eye after her cataract surgery if she could get the flu shot and he told her it was ok. She stated that her tongue started swelling half an hour after she administered her eye drops and 3-4 hours after the flu shot. She stated that they wanted her to take prednisone for 5 days but it made her very sick and stayed in her system for more than a month. She stated that she was now getting back to normal. She stated that her eye drops usually drain into her sinus passage and she experienced a bitter taste on her tongue. This was all the information she provided.  At the time of reporting, the patient had adverse event.  The batch number information was requested.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Parents reported verbal and behavioral tics, previously not demonstrated by this child.  The tics began 2-3 days following administration of DTaP.  Examples of tics include repeatedly speaking the phrase "One more time" while raising a forefinger.  Another example is obsessively and ritually touching both sides of a  playground slide before descending.   A provisional diagnosis of new onset tic disorder and Pediatric Autoimmune Neuropsychiatric Disorder Associated with Streptococcal Infections (PANDAS) was considered as a possible cause.  A 5 day course of azithomycin was prescribed beginning 7 days after the tics started.   Initially the patient's tic behaviors did not decrease, however at the time, however at a follow up visit 5 weeks following, the tic behaviors had decreased, but additional OCD-like door-shutting  behaviors had developed.  Parents also felt that language skills had regressed, although they were age-appropriate at the time of the visit.
LAB_DATA: None to date.  Pt was referred for pediatric neurology consult at Hospital.
CUR_ILL: None at time of vaccination.   Recent cough or cold mentioned by parents

Initially felt typical post vaccine flu like symptoms but including more severe shaking chills & extreme tiredness, so took a few day off regular daily activities and wor ; night of day three about 15 minutes after going to bed my back, both sides and then shoulders began to itch uncontrollably & got red. I was unable to relive it with cortisone creme or itch X so orally took 25 mg Benadryl but a half hour later itching still bad so took a second oral .25 Benadryl & finally a third .25 oral dose on the hour . After a total of 75mg Benedryl & a third topical itch x, application I was able to sleep.  This occurred night of day four  also -same topical treatment plus .50 mg benadryl got me to sleep. Day five  again same topical  treatment and only .25 Benadryl. Day six  .25 mg Benadryl also. Saw PCP  about 4 days later and we agreed I must stop all famvir or similar drugs to see if this would lessen this effect. Additionally from day four on,  if I took a shower even with cool water my arms & legs where water hit itched & burned badly as if many needles being jammed into my skin.  I remain off all famvir type meds but now  12.31.2019 a lukewarm to cool shower made arms burn itch & tun so red I had to get out of shower &rinse off with pitcher slowly in tears from pain & itching.  I am  unable to resume all normal daily activities  due to generalized itching on neck arms back & legs.
OTHER_MEDS: Synthyroid .15 mg daily;  Dexilant 60mg daily A.M;  Famotodine 40mg daily P.M.;  Famvir 250mg 2 X daily; Alive Women over 50 multivite daily ; Lipoflavinoid 2 X daily; Magnesium 300 mg daily ; vite D 2,000 IU daily ;

I was 45 minutes into a zumba class. I started yawning repeatedly, which is very unusual for me. My feet were not obeying orders. I stopped to drink some water and left the studio in case I was dehydrated or overheated; neither helped. I went back into the studio but was unable to keep up with the music so I sat on the floor until the class ended. I started feeling better but my classmates took me to the ER at Hospital, where a series of doctors, nurses, and techs did a number of examinations, labs, and images over the next five hours. They all showed normal results and I was released.
LAB_DATA: BP, pulse, blood (twice), urine; x-ray, CAT scan, MRI; neurological, balance, mobility, etc. EVERYTHING was normal!
